Title: crunchy_maple_almond_walnut_granola
instructions: 1. ﻿﻿﻿Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat. 2. ﻿﻿﻿In a large bowl, mix the oats, walnuts, hemp seeds, cinnamon, and salt together. 3. ﻿﻿﻿In a small saucepan, melt the avocado oil and peanut butter until combined. Remove from the heat and add the maple syrup and vanilla. 4. ﻿﻿﻿Pour the wet mixture over the oats mixture and stir until completely combined. 5. ﻿﻿﻿Dump the granola mixture onto the prepared pan in a single even layer. 6. ﻿﻿﻿Bake for about 12 minutes, press the granola down, then bake for another 7 minutes, or until golden brown. 7. ﻿﻿﻿Allow the granola to cool on the pan completely (about 45 minutes) before breaking into clusters.

Title: Sautéed_chicken_breast
instructions: 1. Pat down chicken breast on both sides with a paper towel. 2. Butterfly the breast by slicing down the middle or hammer it down to the same thickness throughout. 3. Season well with salt, garlic powder, onion powder, and pepper. 4. Heat olive oil and butter in a pan over medium/low heat. 5. When hot, place in chicken breasts and let cook until about 115 internal temp and seared. 6. Flip over and cook until internal of 157. 7. Let sit in either tin foil or a cutting board for at least 5 minutes to finish cooking. 8. Slice and enjoy.
